<dl id="n03004e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n03" href="#n03004e">N03 (VI.B.3)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n03all.htm#n03004e"> 4(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> went away of / his fathers <small>Blue</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n03004e"> <li>FW prototext </li><li><ms href="#n03004e">MS BL 47478-277</ms> </li><li>JJA 52:187 <a name="l45d" href="../../ff/fdra/lda.htm#l45d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/l/l45d.htm#n03004e">Draft: II.2&sect;4.5</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources"> <font color="green">[St. Colmcille on his approaching death]</font> &ldquo;This day,&rdquo; he said, &ldquo;is in the sacred volume called the &lsquo;Sabbath&rsquo;, which is interpreted &lsquo;Rest&rsquo;, and today is truly a Sabbath for me, because it is the last day with me of this present toilsome life, upon which after all my toils and sorrows, I come to enjoy my Sabbath; and at the approaching hour of midnight, as the hallowed day of the Lord begins, I shall, as the Scripture saith, <mark>be going the way of my fathers</mark>. <small> J.M. Flood, <a name="JMFI" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JMFI"><cite title="source">Ireland: Its Saints and Scholars</cite></a> (n.d) 27</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
